title: Grateful Dead Live at Autzen Stadium, U. of Oregon on 1990-06-23
description: Feel Like A Stranger-> West L.A. Fadeaway, Me & My Uncle, Cumberland Blues, Far From Me, They Love Each Other, Cassidy, Tennessee Jed, Promised Land Eyes Of The World, Looks Like Rain-> Crazy Fingers-> Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> I Need A Miracle-> Morning Dew, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Solid Show, A bit "flat" sound wise I've got to believe the original source of this is a Healy Matrix like all the other shows from this June '90 West Coast tour. You can clearly hear some audience coming through. Great show, a bit flat on the sound though. The show really takes off in the second set with the Crazy Fingers>Playin>Uncle John's>Playin. Tons of energy and heavy Phil.

Source Correct? This one could pass for an audience recording upon first listen. Are we sure of the source for this. I know it's not a DSBD and it's questionable that it's even a Healy Matrix. Just sounds like there's too much air. 

As for the show. Solid but unspectacular. Garcia flubs a little in "West L.A." but other than that its a decent show. Second set is fun, "Dew" soars. 

I wouldn't dl this one, there's just too many better shows from this year.
